#DESCRIPTION
#  Find 2 critical point of a cubic polynomial and determine
#  whether the polynomial increases or decreases on the intervals
#  involving the critical points.
#ENDDESCRIPTION
## Author('Utah ww group')
## Institution('Univeristy of Utah')
## DBsubject('Calculus')
## DBchapter('Applications of Differentiation')
## DBsection('Summary of Curve Sketching')
## AuthorText1('Dale Varberg, Edwin J. Purcell, and Steven E. Rigdon')
## TitleText1('Calculus')
## EditionText1('9')
## Section1('Applications of the Derivative')
## Problem1('')
## KEYWORDS('calculus')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = -$coef3 x^3 + $coef2 x^2 - $coef1 x + $coef0 \).
For this function there are three important intervals:
 \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B] \), and \( [B,\infty) \) where
 \( A \) and  \( B \) are the critical points
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is increasing (type in INC) or decreasing (type in DEC).
$BR
\( (-\infty, A] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [A,B] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [B,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
&ANS(std_str_cmp($ans));
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
